title: The Penguins - Earth Angel - 2-disc set (VBR)
description:
The Penguins - Earth Angel: The Cool Sounds of West Coast Doo Wop 1954-1960 (VBR)

The Penguins were a one-hit doo-wop quartet that formed in LA in 1954. They're best known for their hit "Earth Angel" which made the top of the R&B charts and climbed to number 8 on pop charts in 1955. Although the group produced a lot of good doo wop tunes, they were never able to duplicate the success of "Earth Angel".  The group disbanded in 1959.
